<section>
<h2 id="course-overview">Course overview</h2>
<ul>
<li class="fragment">In this class, we'll explore general logical notions in a rigorous and <em>formal</em> way.</li>
<li class="fragment">We'll introduce a specific <em>logical system</em>, define <em>rules</em> that govern that system, and use the rules to construct <em>proofs</em> within the system.</li>
<li class="fragment">Logic is a tool for studying human reasoning and its relation to the world around us.
<li class="fragment">Logic is <em>topic neutral</em>.</li>
<li class="fragment">There is a high reliance on <em>abstraction</em>.</li>
<li class="fragment">Much of what we do will look a lot like what you might see in a math class, specifically <em>algebra</em>.</li>
</ul>
</section>

